&lt;script async defer src=&#34;//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Greetings - I&amp;rsquo;m a software developer based in &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/Bangalore&#34;&gt;Bangalore,
India&lt;/a&gt;. Many years ago I wrote blogs while
going through college at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.iiit.ac.in&#34;&gt;IIIT-H&lt;/a&gt;. As life took
over and the dayjob paid the bills, I lost touch with blogging. Back then
blogging was a big deal and I used to read the ilks of
&lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/meghalomania&#34;&gt;Meghalomania&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://krishashok.me/&#34;&gt;Krish
Ashok&lt;/a&gt;. Facebook and Twitter soon killed away the gusto
of bloggers but given the vitriolic atmosphere of these platforms
long-form makes a lot more sense now. It&amp;rsquo;s the return of the bloggers!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This blog is meant to express my thoughts about
&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/vogxn&#34;&gt;software&lt;/a&gt;, politics, india,
&lt;a href=&#34;https://instagram.com/vogxn&#34;&gt;photography&lt;/a&gt;,
&lt;a href=&#34;https://soundcloud.com/vogonjeltz8423/&#34;&gt;music&lt;/a&gt;, cooking, gardening,
&lt;a href=&#34;https://xkcd.com/386/&#34;&gt;people-being-wrong-on-the-internet&lt;/a&gt; and so on.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
